Puffed brown rice is a versatile, crunchy, and healthy ingredient that can add texture and flavor to many dishes. It’s not only a gluten-free option but also a great source of fiber, antioxidants, and essential nutrients. If you’re looking to incorporate this nutritious grain into your meals, here are some easy and delicious recipes using puffed brown rice that you can try.
1. Puffed Brown Rice GranolaGranola is a breakfast favorite that can be customized with various ingredients. Puffed brown rice adds a light, airy crunch to the mix, making it a perfect base for your granola.
Ingredients:
2 cups puffed brown rice
1 cup rolled oats
½ cup honey or maple syrup
¼ cup coconut oil, melted
½ cup nuts (almonds, walnuts, or cashews), chopped
½ cup dried fruit (raisins, cranberries, or goji berries)
1 tsp vanilla extract
1 tsp ground cinnamon
A pinch of sal
Instructions:
Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the puffed brown rice, rolled oats, and chopped nuts.
In a separate small bowl, mix together the honey, melted coconut oil, vanilla extract, cinnamon, and salt.
Pour the wet mixture over the dry ingredients and stir until everything is evenly coated.
Spread the mixture onto the prepared baking sheet and bake for 15-20 minutes, stirring halfway through, until golden brown.
Remove from the oven, let it cool, and stir in the dried fruit.
Store your granola in an airtight container for up to two weeks. Enjoy it with yogurt or milk for a wholesome breakfast!
Puffed Brown Rice Energy BarsFor a quick and nutritious snack, these puffed brown rice energy bars are perfect. Packed with healthy fats, protein, and fiber, they’re a great on-the-go option.
Ingredients:
2 cups puffed brown rice
1 cup nut butter (peanut butter, almond butter, or sunflower seed butter)
½ cup honey or agave syrup
¼ cup chia seeds
1/4 cup flaxseeds
½ tsp vanilla extract
A pinch of salt
Optional: dark chocolate chips, dried fruit, or coconut flakes
Instructions:
In a large mixing bowl, combine the puffed brown rice, chia seeds, flaxseeds, and salt.
In a small saucepan, heat the nut butter and honey over medium heat, stirring constantly until the mixture is smooth and well combined.
Remove from heat and add vanilla extract.
Pour the wet mixture over the dry ingredients and stir to combine. If desired, mix in chocolate chips, dried fruit, or coconut flakes.
Press the mixture into a lined baking dish, using a spatula to smooth it out evenly.
Refrigerate for at least 1-2 hours to allow the bars to set.
Once set, cut into bars and store in the fridge for up to a week.
3. Puffed Brown Rice and Veggie Stir-FryFor a savory dish, a puffed brown rice stir-fry is a great way to enjoy this crunchy rice with your favorite vegetables.
Ingredients:
1 cup puffed brown rice
1 tbsp olive oil or sesame oil
1 small onion, chopped
1 bell pepper, chopped
1 carrot, julienned
1 zucchini, sliced
2 cloves garlic, minced
2 tbsp soy sauce or tamari
1 tbsp rice vinegar
1 tsp sesame seeds
2 green onions, chopped (for garnish)
Instructions:
Heat the olive or sesame oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat.
Add the chopped onion and garlic, sautéing for 2-3 minutes until fragrant.
Add the bell pepper, carrot, and zucchini. Stir-fry the vegetables for 4-5 minutes, until tender but still crisp.
Add the puffed brown rice to the skillet and stir well, allowing it to toast slightly.
Drizzle in the soy sauce or tamari and rice vinegar, stirring to coat the rice and vegetables.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds and green onions before serving.
This stir-fry can be eaten on its own or served with a side of protein like tofu or chicken.
4. Puffed Brown Rice Smoothie BowlIf you love smoothie bowls, adding puffed brown rice can provide extra texture and crunch to your breakfast or snack.
Ingredients:
1 cup frozen mixed berries
1 ripe banana
½ cup unsweetened almond milk (or any milk of choice)
1 tbsp honey or maple syrup
¼ cup puffed brown rice
Toppings: granola, sliced fruit, chia seeds, shredded coconut, or nuts
Instructions:
In a blender, combine the frozen berries, banana, almond milk, and honey. Blend until smooth.
Pour the smoothie into a bowl and top with puffed brown rice and your favorite toppings like granola, sliced fruit, and chia seeds.
Enjoy this delicious and satisfying breakfast or snack!
5. Puffed Brown Rice Snack MixFor a simple and quick snack, a puffed brown rice snack mix is a great option to munch on throughout the day.
Ingredients:
2 cups puffed brown rice
1 cup mixed nuts (almonds, walnuts, cashews)
½ cup dried fruit (cranberries, raisins, or apricots)
1 tbsp olive oil or melted coconut oil
½ tsp sea salt
1 tsp cinnamon (optional)
¼ tsp chili powder (optional, for a spicy kick)
Instructions:
Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
In a large bowl, combine the puffed brown rice, nuts, and dried fruit.
Drizzle with olive oil or melted coconut oil, and toss to coat.
Sprinkle with sea salt, cinnamon, and chili powder (if using).
Spread the mixture in an even layer on the baking sheet and bake for 10-15 minutes, stirring halfway through, until lightly toasted.
Let the snack mix cool before serving. Store in an airtight container for up to a week.
Conclusion
Puffed brown rice is an incredibly versatile ingredient that can be used in both sweet and savory dishes. Whether you are making a crunchy granola, a savory stir-fry, or a healthy energy bar, puffed brown rice can add an extra layer of texture and flavor. These easy and delicious recipes will help you incorporate this nutritious ingredient into your meals in creative ways. Enjoy experimenting with puffed brown rice in your kitchen!
